This directory implements consistency in three different ways.
The algorithms have overlapping tests to increase confidence.
Examples of how to use this are provided by the applications,
such as factoring, garbage can packing, garbage can coloring,
and critter circuit.

External classes, for users
 * Consistency         - common interface to all of the solvers
 * Constraint          - identifies a pair of inconsistent decisions
 * Problem             - wraps the problem instance
 * NaiveConsistency    - simple exponential algorithm
 * SlightlyLessNaiveConsistencyForFactoring - simple exponential algorithm, for factoring only
 * HadamardConsistency - the real algorithm

Internal classes, not for users
 * Position          - describes the positions of nodes within butterflies
 * Utility           - odds and ends
 * EquationButterfly - part of equation butterflies
 * EquationNode      - part of equation butterflies
 * EquationPair      - part of equation butterflies
 * SolutionButterfly - part of solution butterflies
 * SolutionNode      - part of solution butterflies
 * SolutionPair      - part of solution butterflies

 
Note: the Equation classes could be called "TermPairs", "TermNodes", and "TermButterfly"
 